# P2P Layer Complete Rewrite

Complete rewrite of the P2P networking layer for committee-based consensus, Turbine erasure-coded block propagation, subnet-based gossip, and layered DDoS protection. All files will be production-ready with zero TODOs.

## Proposed Changes

### P2P Types

#### [MODIFY] [types.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/types.zig)

Rewrite with:
- Expanded message codes (shreds, attestations, committee handshake, subnet gossip, view-change, QC)
- `ShredMsg`, `AttestationMsg`, `QuorumCertificate`, `ViewChangeMsg`, `CommitteeHandshakeMsg`
- `SubnetID`, `CommitteeAssignment` types
- Stake-weighted rate limit config constants

---

### Peer Management

#### [MODIFY] [peer.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/peer.zig)

Rewrite with:
- `PeerRole` enum (Validator, RPCRelay, LightNode)
- Stake amount tracking for rate limit calculation
- Subnet membership (list of subscribed subnets)
- Committee membership tracking (current committee, role)
- Connection budget enforcement (max 512 connections)
- Reputation scoring with decay (score decays toward 0 over time)
- Bandwidth tracking per peer (bytes sent/received)
- Automatic disconnect on score < threshold

---

### Peer Discovery

#### [MODIFY] [discovery.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/discovery.zig)

Rewrite with:
- Full Kademlia implementation with proper PING/PONG/FIND_NODE/NEIGHBORS
- Subnet-aware discovery: prioritize peers in same subnets
- Bootstrap node list support
- ENR (Ethereum Node Record) v4 encoding with validator address attestation
- Periodic refresh of routing table (every 5 minutes)
- Stale node eviction (LRU within buckets)

---

### Compression

#### [MODIFY] [compression.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/compression.zig)

Rewrite with:
- Snappy compression (frame format) for fast network compression
- Fallback to raw if compression produces larger output
- Thread-safe (stateless design — no mutable state in compressor)
- Proper error handling for corrupt/truncated data on decompress

---

### Turbine Block Propagation

#### [MODIFY] [turbine.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/turbine.zig)

Complete rewrite with:
- GF(2^8) Reed-Solomon erasure coding (encode + decode)
- Configurable data/parity shred counts based on block size
- `PropagationTree` struct: stake-weighted tree assignment with configurable fanout
- Shred signature verification (producer signs each shred)
- `ShredCollector` with proper RS recovery (not XOR)
- Block size adaptive: auto-calculate shred count for any block size
- Bandwidth-aware: respect per-layer bandwidth budget

---

### Gulf Stream Transaction Forwarding

#### [MODIFY] [gulf_stream.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/gulf_stream.zig)

Rewrite with:
- Batch size 4096 (up from 256)
- Transaction compression via Compressor before forwarding
- VRF-based leader prediction (wired to actual committee selection)
- Redundant forwarding to next 2 predicted leaders (backup)
- Forward queue with expiry (drop batches older than 2 slots)
- Rate limiting: max forward throughput per slot
- Statistics: forwarded count, hit rate, miss rate, latency

---

### P2P Server

#### [MODIFY] [server.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/p2p/server.zig)

Complete rewrite with:
- **Subnet Architecture**: 64 attestation subnets, each node subscribes to 2
- **Committee-Aware Routing**: Shreds go via Turbine tree; attestations via subnet gossip
- **Batch I/O**: `sendmmsg`/`recvmmsg` on Linux, sequential fallback on macOS
- **Configurable Thread Pool**: `num_workers` (default 8, configurable)
- **Layered DDoS Defense**:
  - Layer 1: Connection budget (max 512 persistent connections)
  - Layer 2: Stake-weighted token bucket rate limiting (refill proportional to sqrt(stake))
  - Layer 3: Committee members get 10× burst allowance during their active slot
- **Message Handlers**: Status, Shreds, Attestations, QC, ViewChange, TX batches, NodeData, SlashEvidence
- **Peer Lifecycle**: Auto-disconnect peers with score below -100, periodic pruning
- **Statistics**: Packets in/out, bandwidth, peer count, subnet health

---

